Nationals of the following countries do not require a visa if their passports are endorsed "for public affairs":
}
In addition:
* Holders of a valid Type "C" multiple entry visa or Permanent Residency for the Schengen Area may enter Macedonia for up to 15 days visa free. A temporary residence permit is not accepted. (On some Permanent Residence Cards there is an expiration date, which would be a cause for the Residence Permit Holder not to be allowed to enter Macedonia)
* Holders of a valid UK, Canada or USA visa may enter Macedonia for up to 15 days visa free.
* Holders of UN travel documents do not require a visa.
APPROVAL
Section::::Approval.
In addition to a visa, nationals of Afghanistan, Algeria, Angola, Bangladesh, Burundi, Cameroon, China, Congo, Egypt, Ethiopia, Gabon, Ghana, Guatemala, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Honduras, Iran, Iraq, Jordan, Lebanon, Libya, Morocco, Niger, Nigeria, Oman, Pakistan, Philippines, Rwanda, Saudi Arabia, Senegal, Somalia, Sudan, Syria, Tunisia, Vietnam and Yemen need approval from the Ministry of Interior.
DIPLOMATIC AND OFFICIAL PASSPORTS
Section::::Diplomatic and official passports.
Additionally, only holders of diplomatic and official passports of the following countries do not require visas for Macedonia:
RECIPROCITY
Section::::Reciprocity.
Macedonian citizens can enter some of the countries whose citizens are granted visa-free access to Macedonia without a visa but they require a visa for Antigua and Barbuda, Australia, Azerbaijan, Barbados, Brunei, Canada, Ireland, Kazakhstan, Mauritius (grants visa on arrival), Mexico, New Zealand, Paraguay, Saint Kitts and Nevis, South Korea, Taiwan (grants visa on arrival), United Arab Emirates, United Kingdom, United States, Uruguay and Venezuela.
